title: For Sale:  Firearms International Co PreGarcia Bronco .22 Single Shot Skeleton Rifle
postcontent:
Single shot, lightweight rifle with a skeletonized cast metal frame, likely zinc. There do not appear to be any cracks in the stock.  The barrel rotates for loading of a single .22 caliber round.

This rifle has most of its original finish with even patina. The barrel and stock have a few scratches here and there, bore is clean bright and the rifling is sharp.  The initials and numerals "ODL 857232" are engraved on one side. The action functions correctly, but I have not fired this rifle since I acquired it.

The overall condition of this rifle is very good.  A unique piece with an unusual design that must be seen to be appreciated.

The year of manufacture is unknown, but it has older Firearms International cast markings “FIREARMS INTERNATIONAL CORPORATION / WASHINGTON D.C. 20022” which suggest that it was imported prior to the 1968 gun control act.

So-called skeleton rifles became popular in the late 1800’s among cyclists, giving them the name “Bicycle Guns”. These rifles were not for the protection of cyclists, but it was common for someone to ride their bike to their favorite hunting spot. The lightweight and compactness made for a perfect companion. Now these rifles serve as great survival rifles with their solid robust design and compactness stashing away nicely in the truck, camper, or boat. These unusual little rifles don’t come up often, so don't wait too long. 

OREGON RESIDENTS ONLY for pick up. No trades, cash only. REDACTED.

This is a very unique item: For a very short time, Luigi Franchi, the famed shotgun maker from Brescia, made a very limited amt of .22 rifles called the Para Takedown. title: For Sale:  Hi Point Carbine Oversize Magazine Release
postcontent:
Oversize magazine release for all the Hi Point carbines.
These fit the classic, TS, and ATI stocks.
This button increases the diameter of the magazine release to .500 diameter. They are machined from billet 6061 aluminum. These are a 2 piece unit, inner adaptor and outer button.
I have 2 textures available either knurled or radial grooved. You also have your choice of either bare aluminum or black anodized. 
These buttons improve the ability of the shooter to release the magazine in high stress situations and or while using gloves. 
These are a direct drop in on the .40/.45 caliber carbines. 
On the 9mm guns in either the classic or TS stock the original latch pin does need to be shortened about .100 that information is included in instructions. This is a simple process usually done with a bench grinder or dremel tool.
When ordering please specify which texture and which color so I ship what you request.
If you have any questions please feel free to contact me.
Price includes shipping,
Preferred payment is Paypal.
Scott

title: For Sale:  Backpack, Special Ops Vietnam era
postcontent:
This is an in-country made pack for SOG units operating in Laos and Cambodia.  The SF units operating outside of Vietnam needed "sterile" gear and weapons so that their activities could not be blamed on the United States if captured.  There are no markings on it whatsoever.

The rucksack itself is designed similar the the ALICE pack, with three pockets on the front.  Each pocket has two male snaps for different packing adjustments.  The main interior pocket is larger that an ALICE medium, and slightly smaller than the large.  There is a waist belt, and I added a black sternum strap (easily removed if unwanted).  The frame appears to be a metal tubular WWII/Korea era Mountain ruck.
